## Explanation

### What is a server?

A server is a computer that provides services, resources, or data to other computers (clients) over a network.

### What is the role of the domain name?

The domain name (foobar.com) provides a human-readable address that allows users to access the website without remembering the server IP address.

### What type of DNS record is www in www.foobar.com?

The www record is an A record that points to the IPv4 address 8.8.8.8.

### What is the role of the web server (Nginx)?

The web server receives HTTP/HTTPS requests from clients, serves static content, and forwards dynamic requests to the application server.

### What is the role of the application server?

The application server executes the application code, processes requests, interacts with the database, and generates responses.

### What is the role of the database (MySQL)?

The database stores and manages application data such as users, products, orders, and other information.

### What is the server using to communicate with the user's computer?

The server communicates with the client using HTTP or HTTPS over the TCP/IP protocol suite.

## Issues with this infrastructure

### Single Point of Failure (SPOF)

There is only one server. If the server fails, the entire website becomes unavailable.

### Downtime during maintenance

When deploying new code or restarting services such as Nginx or the application server, the website may become temporarily unavailable.

### Cannot scale

Because all components run on a single server, the infrastructure cannot efficiently handle a large amount of incoming traffic.
